More Notes: Farm incomes are 4% higher on average compared to the deterministic scenario.
Cereal production is on average 9 % lower.
Mean farm income increases more than in scenarios with only one source of uncertainty.
Land use and farm labor are negatively affected compared to the deterministic case.
11 per cent increase in the mean yields for cereals in 2050 in the economic model compared to the base year.
Simulated seasonal timothy grass & spring wheat yields significantly higher under projected climate conditions.
Impact of uncertainty on red meat production - a slight decrease assumed to be in unit terms.
Impact of uncertainty on white meat production - an expansion assumed to be in unit terms.
Climate uncertainty leads to lower feeding costs due to yield changes, impacting white meat production - qualitative not quantitative
